name: Bhalamander Zabba
description: During The Long Drought of Malamesh there was a man named Bhalamander Zabba. He was a simple farmer who lived alone in the region of Kurtafal. It was told that one day, Bhalamander had only one last glass of water to drink and when he was about to drink it, he saw a lizard in the brink of death. Bhalamander then decided to give his last glass of water to the dying lizard. and as soon as the lizard touch the water, rain fell upon the scorched land.
